title: CALLING FOR FREE AND FAIR PARLIAMENTARY ELECTIONS IN THE REPUBLIC OF  AZERBAIJAN

content.text:
The SPEAKER pro tempore. The unfinished business is the question of 
suspending the rules and agreeing to the resolution, H. Res. 326, as 
amended.
content.speaker: The SPEAKER pro tempore

content.text: The Clerk read the title of the resolution.
content.speaker: The Clerk

content.text:
The SPEAKER pro tempore. The question is on the motion offered by the 
gentlewoman from Florida (Ms. Ros-Lehtinen) that the House suspend the 
rules and agree to the resolution, H. Res. 326, as amended, on which 
the yeas and nays are ordered.
  This will be a 5-minute vote.
content.speaker: The SPEAKER pro tempore

content.text:
The vote was taken by electronic device, and there were--yeas 416, 
nays 1, not voting 16, as follows:

                             [Roll No. 400]
content.speaker: The RECORDER
